problem:
For all complex numbers $z$, let \[f(z) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
z^{2}&\text{ if }z\text{ is not real}, \\
-z^2 &\text{ if }z\text{ is real}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find $f(f(f(f(1+i))))$.

Find the ratio of the area of $\triangle BCX$ to the area of $\triangle ACX$ in the diagram if $CX$ bisects $\angle ACB$. [asy]
import markers;

real t=32/(32+35);
pair A=(-16.57,0);
pair B=(9.43,0);
pair C=(0,30.65);
pair X=t*A+(1-t)*B;

draw(C--A--B--C--X);

label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,E);
label("$C$",C,N);
label("$X$",X,NE);

label("$28$",.5*(B+A),S);
label("$32$",.5*(B+C),NE);
label("$35$",.5*(A+C),NW);
