Let  $a$  and  $b$  satisfy the conditions  $\begin{cases}
a^3 - 6a^2 + 15a = 9 
b^3 - 3b^2 + 6b = -1 \end{cases}$. Evaluate the value of  $(a - b)^{2014}$.

Let $g$ be defined by  \[g(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
x+3 & \text{ if } x \leq 2, \\
x^2 - 4x + 5 & \text{ if } x > 2.
\end{array}
\right.\]Calculate $g^{-1}(1)+g^{-1}(6)+g^{-1}(11)$.

